org.apertereports.engine
Class ReportMaster

java.lang.Object
  org.apertereports.engine.ReportMaster
All Implemented Interfaces:
ConfigurationConstants, ReportConstants
public class ReportMaster
extends Object
implements ReportConstants, ConfigurationConstants

A workhorse of the Jasper reports engine. This class is responsible for generating, exporting and converting JRXMLs to JasperPrints and later to expected formats.

The static methods of this class should be used to convert the report to whatever format one wants.

In order to maintain the report generation from a template one should create a new instance of this class.

Method Detail

exportReport

public static byte[] exportReport(net.sf.jasperreports.engine.JasperPrint jasperPrint,
                                  String format,
                                  Map<net.sf.jasperreports.engine.JRExporterParameter,Object> exporterParameters,
                                  Map<String,String> configuration)
                           throws AperteReportsException
Exports a JasperPrint to a desired format. The method also takes a customParameters param. These are included unconditionally in the exporter instance used to generate the report.

Currently the only configuration parameter that can be handled is ConfigurationConstants.JASPER_REPORTS_CHARACTER_ENCODING - the character encoding of the output report.

Parameters:
jasperPrint - A JasperPrint
format - Desired output format (i.e. PDF, HTML etc)
exporterParameters - Additional custom JRExporterParameter map
configuration - Configuration parameters
Returns:
Bytes of a generated report
Throws:
AperteReportsException - on error
